OL,7,F"It is clear beyond doubt that you
OL,8,Fsuffer from a serious mental illness
OL,9,Fand that it is appropriate for you to
OL,10,Fbe detained in hospital."
OL,12,FHe continued: "As I have detailed the
OL,13,Fopinions of all the trained
OL,14,Fpsychiatrists is that these offences
OL,15,Fare attributable to your illness.
OL,16,FThere is no other evidence for reason
OL,17,For motivation to commit these offences.
OL,19,F"I am therefore wholly satisfied that
OL,20,Fyour culpability is reduced due to
OL,21,Fyour mental illness.
